  "uuid": "570b1f3ce67f4a8d83c1b6d772ac85f4",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Assistant Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Painting Assistant Project Engineer</strong> </p><p><br /></p><p><u><strong>Description & Requirments</strong></u></p><ul><li>Assist in the development of the Painting/Special Coating project estimates</li><li>Forecast and analyze construction costs, exposures, and profits.</li><li>Develop the schedule for all phases the painting and coatings work.</li><li>Develop and implement project specific processes and procedures associated with Paintings/Coatings.</li><li>In conjunction with the Project Superintendent, lead, direct and coordinate the day-to-day management and construction activities.</li><li>Manage project costs, through ongoing evaluations of labor, material, and equipment</li><li>Interface with all company departments as necessary to resolve any issue.</li><li>Ensure all safety measures, procedures, and requirements are met, followed, and practiced</li><li>Monitor and supervise all vendors or outside contractors to ensure the quality of work and completion of the work before payments are made.</li><li>Must be able to supervise a staff of up to 30</li><li>Ability to meet the physical requirements of the job.</li><li>Must carry a Phone and be available for on call services twenty-four hours.</li><li>Must be proficient in general maintenance including plumbing, electricity, painting, drywall, floorcoverings, carpentry, locks, appliances, pools & spas, roof, city codes and life safety equipment.</li><li>4-6 years relevant project management experience in the</li><li><em><strong>Painting/Special Coatings industry</strong></em></li></ul>",
